{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – an arrow. More recognizable in older forms. Compare [[畀]] and [[至]]. See also the bottom component of [[睪]] and the original versions of [[弗]] and [[𢦏]].

===Etymology 1===
; arrow
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tV-lij||bow (weapon); slingshot}}, with metonymic semantic shift from "bow" to "arrow"; cognate with {{cog|my|လေး||bow; crossbow}}, {{cog|lus|li||spring (as of gun, watch, etc.)}}, {{cog|sit-jap|tɯdi||bow}}, {{m|sit-jap|zdi||arrow}}, {{cog|txg|𘎗||bow}}, {{m|txg|𗮆||arrow}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Hill, 2013}}; {{zh-ref|Jacques, 2014}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques and Lai, 2019}}).
; to swear, to vow
: {{rfe|zh|From sense "arrow"?}}

